               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430403-name-1103" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1103" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1103" type="surname" value="MARSHALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1103" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM MARSHALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a watch and clock maker, and live in the Hackney-road—about a quarter before nine o'clock in the morning of the 18th of March I left my shop, leaving a time-piece on the table—the door was open—I came back about eleven o'clock, and it was gone—I saw it at Marylebone office—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What do you know it by? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> The name and the number—it had not been sold.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430403-name-1104" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1104" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1104" type="surname" value="POWELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1104" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM POWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a shoemaker—on the morning of the 18th of March I was in Bell-street, Marylebone, with Langley—I saw the prisoner with something under his arm, covered with an apron—I went after him—he ran away—I ran and stopped him, and asked what he had got—he did not say; but said it had been given him—I took him, and found it was this time-piece.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Are you in training for the police? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; I have been in the police—I went after the prisoner at Langley's request.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430403-name-1105" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1105" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1105" type="surname" value="EADE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1105" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM EADE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I was in Great James-street—Powell brought me the prisoner and the time-piece, covered over with an apron—I asked the prisoner what he had got—he said he did not know—I asked where he got it—he said a little boy gave it him round the corner—I made inquiries—the prosecutor came and owned it.</p>
